School of Materials Science and Engineering invites applications for the position of Research Fellow.
Key Responsibilities:

  Responsible for the development of nanoCu ink for printing applications
  Support the characterizations of new nanoCu paste from industry partner
  Submission of data for sharing with funder or in publications

Requirements:

  Possess PhD degree in Materials Science/engineering or related disciplines
  Experience in nanomaterials synthesis and/or formulation and  advanced laboratory skills such as DSC, TGA, XRD, AFM, SEM, EDX, TEM, etc

We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.